Day 12: Normalisation – 3NF & BCNF

Topic:
Third Normal Form (3NF) and Boyce-Codd Normal Form (BCNF)

Learning Objectives:

Understand the rules and purpose of Third Normal Form (3NF)
Learn about Boyce-Codd Normal Form (BCNF) and its importance
Understand functional dependencies and how they affect database design
Learn how advanced normalization reduces redundancy and improves consistency
Practice creating well-structured relational schemas

Activities / Deliverables:

Continue the normalization process from previous tables
Convert the database structure into 3NF and BCNF
Identify and resolve functional dependency issues
Draw the final normalized schema diagram
Verify relationships and table structures in MySQL Workbench
Document all normalization steps and observations

Tools / Tech:

MySQL Workbench

